<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 12:06AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Jefferson and northwestern Love Counties through 1245 AM CDT...
At 1206 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles east of Terral, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Leon, Rubottom, Oscar, Courtney and Petersburg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
